{
  "text": "A number of studies have emphasized the importance of the relationship between past experiences, their emotional context and their impact on future actions [CITATION_1] , as people create themselves through memory [55] . Thus, when memories of life events trigger sadness and self-doubt, people often get trapped and negative self-esteem may be related to their sensibility and inability to receive bad feedback [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
